OL,3,CThe 'arrogant' headteacher who
OL,4,Csexually preyed on teenage girls
OL,6,FAt times he could be seen in the dock,
OL,7,Fsat metres away from the press bench,
OL,8,Fputting on reading glasses as he
OL,9,Fforensically examined the evidence
OL,10,Fagainst him.
OL,12,FWhen he took to the stand to defend
OL,13,Fhimself in week three, he spoke
OL,14,Fconfidently and tried to tear apart
OL,15,Fthe evidence of the teens line-by-line.
OL,17,FHe claimed he was "just somebody
OL,18,Fwanting to help". In truth, he had
OL,19,Fpreyed on the girls and sexually
OL,20,Fabused them.
