OL,3,CThe 'arrogant' headteacher who
OL,4,Csexually preyed on teenage girls
OL,6,FWhen asked if he'd had sex with one of
OL,7,Fthe girls, he said a medical condition
OL,8,Fmeant he "couldn't have done, even if
OL,9,FI had wanted to". He added: "There is
OL,10,Fvery little point in arranging a
OL,11,Fsexual liaison I couldn't fulfil".
OL,13,FToday, the seven women and five men of
OL,14,Fthe jury ruled that they did not
OL,15,Fbelieve him.
OL,17,FJudge Rhys Rowlands told the defendant
OL,18,F"some of the explanations for your
OL,19,Fbehaviour towards the victims
OL,20,Fproffered by you beggared belief at
OL,21,Ftimes".
